## 4 Â· Power Series

<definition title="Power Series">
A **power series** centred at <m>a</m> is a series of the form

<math>
\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} c_n (x - a)^n
</math>

The **radius of convergence** is <m>R = \dfrac{1}{\limsup |c_n|^{1/n}}</m>
(Hadamard formula). The series converges absolutely for <m>|x - a| < R</m>.
</definition>

<math plot="true" xmin="-1.5" xmax="1.5" title="Partial sums of ln(1+x) series">
x - x^2/2 + x^3/3 - x^4/4
x - x^2/2 + x^3/3 - x^4/4 + x^5/5 - x^6/6
</math>

