## 7 Â· Problem Set

<steps>
  <step title="Prove or disprove: every subsequence of a convergent sequence converges">
  Use the definition of convergence directly. The same <m>N</m> works for any
  subsequence since <m>n_k \geq k</m>.
  </step>
  <step title="Show that the harmonic series diverges">
  Group terms: <m>\sum 1/n \geq 1 + 1/2 + (1/3 + 1/4) + \ldots \geq \sum 1/2</m>.
  </step>
  <step title="Determine the radius of convergence of \(\sum n^2 x^n\)">
  Apply the ratio test: <m>R = \lim (n+1)^2/n^2 \cdot 1/1 = 1</m>.
  </step>
  <step title="Prove the Cauchyâ€“Hadamard formula">
  Show convergence for <m>|x| < R</m> using root test and divergence for
  <m>|x| > R</m> since terms don't tend to zero.
  </step>
</steps>
